Dude,

299
00:16:54,423 --> 00:16:56,056
Halverson's fine.

300
00:16:57,225 --> 00:16:59,309
- What? Wait! Who? What?
- Bennett.

301
00:17:00,061 --> 00:17:01,686
She's, what?
Like, distinguished?

302
00:17:02,130 --> 00:17:04,773
Like young and fine, I poo you not.

303
00:17:05,065 --> 00:17:06,191
Are we into her?

304
00:17:06,377 --> 00:17:08,109
We may be fierce on the subject.

305
00:17:08,308 --> 00:17:10,208
Oh, God, I wish I was there!

306
00:17:10,555 --> 00:17:11,738
What's she like?

307
00:17:12,303 --> 00:17:13,438
Totally shy,

308
00:17:13,563 --> 00:17:15,417
librarian energy through the roof.

309
00:17:15,542 --> 00:17:17,118
- <i>Glasses?</i>
- Glasses on a chain!

310
00:17:17,451 --> 00:17:18,543
For the win!

311
00:17:18,668 --> 00:17:21,099
<i>Dude, she has a dead arm!</i>

312
00:17:21,224 --> 00:17:23,833
Like, dead?
Like, in a sling, with the glove?

313
00:17:24,344 --> 00:17:27,394
Imagine John Cassavetes
in <i>The Fury</i> as a hot chick.

314
00:17:27,592 --> 00:17:29,005
Which you know I often have.

315
00:17:31,710 --> 00:17:33,019
We lose the connection?

316
00:17:33,144 --> 00:17:35,011
Dude, she's probably an Active!

317
00:17:38,511 --> 00:17:40,061
You're so untrusting.

318
00:17:50,991 --> 00:17:51,991
Bree?

319
00:17:54,699 --> 00:17:56,199
Don't go. Don't go.

320
00:17:56,367 --> 00:17:58,243
We have to go. Come on!

321
00:18:03,875 --> 00:18:05,125
Don't leave me!

322
00:18:12,133 --> 00:18:13,883
I'm not gonna leave you.
We're both going.

323
00:18:14,233 --> 00:18:15,233
Now!

324
00:18:24,084 --> 00:18:25,353
Good-bye, Caroline.

325
00:18:42,445 --> 00:18:43,596
Are you okay?

326
00:18:44,396 --> 00:18:45,331
What happened?

327
00:18:46,305 --> 00:18:47,595
Here, come here, come here.

328
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:50,401
Look at me. Look at me.
Can you tell me what happened?

329
00:18:50,905 --> 00:18:51,755
It was Echo.

330
00:18:52,995 --> 00:18:53,810
Oh, boy.

331
00:18:53,935 --> 00:18:54,935
Oh, boy!

332
00:18:57,225 --> 00:18:58,225
Bad!

333
00:19:01,135 --> 00:19:02,285
Where is she?

334
00:19:03,435 --> 00:19:04,726
She took Perrin.

335
00:19:12,925 --> 00:19:14,125
Bree, wait.

336
00:19:14,525 --> 00:19:16,325
I'm not Bree. I'm Echo.

337
00:19:16,845 --> 00:19:18,400
Echo, what did they do to you?

338
00:19:18,525 --> 00:19:20,525
She did this. But not to me.

339
00:19:20,860 --> 00:19:23,560
She? Who? I don't understand.
Who is "she"?

340
00:19:25,623 --> 00:19:27,582
- Don't leave me!
- Sorry, sister.

341
00:19:27,865 --> 00:19:29,715
I stay, we both get nabbed.

342
00:19:33,575 --> 00:19:35,775
She wanted me to know how it felt.

343
00:19:36,384 --> 00:19:37,534
It feels bad.

344
00:19:37,969 --> 00:19:40,447
You're not making any sense.
Were they imprinting you?

345
00:19:40,595 --> 00:19:42,722
You don't seem finished.

346
00:19:42,995 --> 00:19:44,724
How do you know
when you're finished?

347
00:19:46,686 --> 00:19:49,103
Listen to me. I think someone
on the inside is trying to help us.

348
00:19:49,271 --> 00:19:51,905
They showed me the way out,
put it in my head so we could escape.

349
00:19:52,030 --> 00:19:53,480
We haven't escaped.

350
00:19:53,635 --> 00:19:55,276
They're coming, they always come.

351
00:19:56,165 --> 00:19:57,445
Because of this.

352
00:19:59,115 --> 00:20:00,215
What's that?

353
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:07,212
- It's how they find us.
- GPS tag?

354
00:20:09,165 --> 00:20:10,375
We have to cut.

355
00:20:43,145 --> 00:20:44,645
I don't think I can.

356
00:20:46,615 --> 00:20:47,615
You will.

357
00:20:48,955 --> 00:20:50,248
I'll show you how.

358
00:20:51,705 --> 00:20:53,540
That's where Senator Perrin
will sit.

359
00:20:53,665 --> 00:20:56,462
He's gonna make an opening statement,
and then the hearing will begin.

360
00:20:56,805 --> 00:20:58,798
Okay, this is the press area here,
so just...

361
00:20:59,585 --> 00:21:02,385
be prepared for a couple dozen
camera lenses pointing at you.

362
00:21:02,805 --> 00:21:03,990
A couple dozen?

363
00:21:04,115 --> 00:21:07,565
Don't even think about that.
Just focus on your testimony.

364
00:21:08,795 --> 00:21:10,018
Where is the senator now?

365
00:21:10,945 --> 00:21:13,396
He's following up on some last minute
evidence we received.

366
00:21:14,065 --> 00:21:17,315
He wants all the ammunition
against Rossum we can get.

367
00:21:18,945 --> 00:21:20,495
Excuse me one moment.

368
00:21:21,475 --> 00:21:23,325
- Hello?
- <i>Perrin escaped.</i>

369
00:21:24,115 --> 00:21:25,115
I see.

370
00:21:25,915 --> 00:21:27,744
Can you explain how that happened?

371
00:21:27,912 --> 00:21:31,289
He was attacked by that LA Active, Echo.
They're together.

372
00:21:32,045 --> 00:21:33,666
- Has he been wiped?
- <i>No.</i>

373
00:21:33,885 --> 00:21:35,418
That is very unfortunate.

374
00:21:35,586 --> 00:21:38,140
We tracked their GPS,
we dispatched a retrieval team.

375
00:21:38,265 --> 00:21:40,798
I've sent you the coordinates.
You need to be there when it goes down.

376
00:21:41,216 --> 00:21:42,216
On my way.

377
00:22:44,145 --> 00:22:45,845
They won't stop looking.

378
00:22:47,295 --> 00:22:48,895
We won't stop running.

379
00:22:50,105 --> 00:22:51,370
Pull everybody in.

380
00:22:51,495 --> 00:22:52,745
I want every team on this.

381
00:22:53,615 --> 00:22:55,115
Well, figure it out!

382
00:22:56,155 --> 00:22:59,877
He has to be at that hearing in 4 hours,
or Rossum will have our heads.

383
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:03,010
To be clear, this little project
is your problem, not mine.

384
00:23:03,135 --> 00:23:06,009
Well, I'll remind you of that
when we're bunk buddies in the Attic.

385
00:23:08,055 --> 00:23:09,305
Listen to this.

386
00:23:10,045 --> 00:23:11,466
She's got a great idea.

387
00:23:12,266 --> 00:23:14,195
It's your idea.
It's based on your idea.

388
00:23:14,925 --> 00:23:16,894
But you should tell them.
I can't take the credit.

389
00:23:17,225 --> 00:23:18,271
Spit it out!

390
00:23:18,439 --> 00:23:20,741
We might be able
to reconfigure the disruptor

391
00:23:20,866 --> 00:23:24,110
to incapacitate Echo and Perrin
without actually locating them.

392
00:23:24,835 --> 00:23:25,835
Explain.

393
00:23:27,755 --> 00:23:30,679
Topher's disruptor sends a signal
using a universal frequency,

394
00:23:30,804 --> 00:23:34,030
which affects every Doll,
but only within a limited range.

395
00:23:34,155 --> 00:23:36,998
If we use the neural electric biolinks,
we can redirect the loop

396
00:23:37,166 --> 00:23:38,666
to target a specific brain.

397
00:23:38,834 --> 00:23:39,884
In English.

398
00:23:41,945 --> 00:23:44,145
I do the English part? That's new.

399
00:23:45,895 --> 00:23:48,075
We can plug my disruptor
into the biolink system

400
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,553
and send the signal from here
and put them to sleep.

401
00:23:50,995 --> 00:23:54,045
A painful, bleeding sleep,
but sleep, nonetheless.

402
00:23:54,365 --> 00:23:55,865
Right? She's just...

403
00:23:56,165 --> 00:23:57,915
Genius! She's so good!

404
00:23:59,755 --> 00:24:02,065
- How long will this take to accomplish?
- Not long at all.

405
00:24:02,233 --> 00:24:05,733
I can have Echo's brain map
uploaded into Bennett's system.

406
00:24:05,895 --> 00:24:07,420
I just need Perrin's.

407
00:24:07,545 --> 00:24:09,145
I gotta have a target.

408
00:24:09,531 --> 00:24:11,381
Give him whatever he needs.

409
00:24:15,645 --> 00:24:16,895
Topher Brink...

410
00:24:18,775 --> 00:24:20,225
Meet Daniel Perrin.

411
00:24:27,235 --> 00:24:30,285
It may be the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

412
00:24:36,705 --> 00:24:40,405
Selective strand replacement
takes a delicate hand.

413
00:24:41,045 --> 00:24:42,720
This is more
than just an alteration.

414
00:24:42,845 --> 00:24:46,180
This is an imprint married to a...

415
00:24:46,305 --> 00:24:47,693
an existing consciousness.

416
00:24:48,495 --> 00:24:51,280
It's amazing you didn't end up
with a schizophrenic.

417
00:24:51,448 --> 00:24:55,201
I have a theory that the brain can hold
multiple imprints and still function.

418
00:24:55,705 --> 00:24:57,905
- A composite?
- Not a composite.

419
00:24:58,080 --> 00:24:59,080
Something new.

420
00:24:59,385 --> 00:25:01,935
The original Daniel Perrin
is all there.

421
00:25:02,585 --> 00:25:03,585
I just...

422
00:25:03,975 --> 00:25:05,275
made him better.

423
00:25:07,615 --> 00:25:09,507
We'll need your Active's map.

424
00:25:16,075 --> 00:25:17,075
Uploaded.

425
00:25:22,455 --> 00:25:23,705
It's very nice.

426
00:25:24,745 --> 00:25:26,845
She was kind of a hooker.

427
00:25:30,645 --> 00:25:31,745
How about...

428
00:25:32,114 --> 00:25:34,214
While I build the magic bullets,

429
00:25:34,665 --> 00:25:36,665
you work on adapting your gun?

430
00:25:38,345 --> 00:25:39,495
Right. Right.

431
00:25:40,175 --> 00:25:43,175
You can use the whole workspace
over there.

432
00:25:52,815 --> 00:25:55,354
Let's hope when we zap them,
they're not driving down the freeway

433
00:25:55,479 --> 00:25:57,929
or flying a biplane
or something, huh?

434
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:08,274


435
00:26:09,096 --> 00:26:11,170
You probably don't even need
to make delivery files.

436
00:26:11,295 --> 00:26:14,040
I bet we can just plug this baby
straight into your biofeed...

437
00:26:14,165 --> 00:26:15,515
I know. I just...

438
00:26:16,395 --> 00:26:18,618
thought I'd upload some sweet dreams
to pass along.

439
00:26:18,743 --> 00:26:19,785


440
00:26:20,285 --> 00:26:22,885
Compensate for the searing,
searing pain.

441
00:26:25,645 --> 00:26:26,745
I like that.

442
00:26:36,146 --> 00:26:37,950
- Incoming.
- Is that it?

443
00:26:38,075 --> 00:26:39,347
It's me. The him-me.

444
00:26:39,515 --> 00:26:42,815
- I'm giving the word to myself.
- And what's the word?

445
00:26:43,268 --> 00:26:44,668
It ain't "Grease".

446
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:47,830
The he-me did it.

447
00:26:47,955 --> 00:26:49,524
I rock. We rock.

448
00:26:51,195 --> 00:26:53,569
The I-other-me has accessed
Perrin's brain map.

449
00:26:55,668 --> 00:26:58,824
That may be the most beautiful
thing I have ever seen.

450
00:27:05,643 --> 00:27:07,208
We can't stay here to long.

451
00:27:08,254 --> 00:27:09,254
It's real.

452
00:27:10,338 --> 00:27:12,888
It's all real.
They didn't program this.

453
00:27:13,703 --> 00:27:14,953
I grew up here.

454
00:27:18,260 --> 00:27:19,560
I wish they had.

455
00:27:20,943 --> 00:27:21,943
Why?

456
00:27:22,940 --> 00:27:25,293
They didn't create me.
Only parts of me.

457
00:27:25,418 --> 00:27:27,348
How can I ever untangle it?

458
00:27:27,563 --> 00:27:28,604
Does it matter?

459
00:27:31,551 --> 00:27:32,737
What do you mean?

460
00:27:32,862 --> 00:27:34,443
Does it matter who you were?

461
00:27:35,020 --> 00:27:37,655
All that matters is
who you decide to be. Who you can be.

462
00:27:38,294 --> 00:27:39,740
You make it sound so easy.

463
00:27:40,488 --> 00:27:42,660
It is.
It's all up to you.

464
00:27:42,785 --> 00:27:44,287
What, the voters don't get a say?

465
00:27:44,759 --> 00:27:46,622
The voters will say yes.

466
00:27:49,527 --> 00:27:50,677
I don't know.

467
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,160
At this stage,

468
00:27:52,860 --> 00:27:54,707
might seem a little cynical.

469
00:27:54,832 --> 00:27:56,966
Like I was trading in
on the family name.

470
00:27:57,229 --> 00:27:58,505
Oh, you would be.

471
00:27:58,630 --> 00:28:00,177
But it wouldn't be cynical.

472
00:28:00,649 --> 00:28:02,096
You use what you have.

473
00:28:02,264 --> 00:28:03,973
Think of all the good you could do.

474
00:28:06,749 --> 00:28:08,599
Even if I decided to run...

475
00:28:10,431 --> 00:28:12,777
Do you have any idea
how much dirt the opposition

476
00:28:12,902 --> 00:28:14,298
could throw at me?

477
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:17,973
I saw what you were doing
when I walked into this party.

478
00:28:19,213 --> 00:28:21,145
But everybody's got a past.

479
00:28:21,850 --> 00:28:24,300
It's the future
the voters care about.

480
00:28:24,888 --> 00:28:27,488
You show them that, all
will be forgiven.

481
00:28:30,685 --> 00:28:31,876
Where did you come from?

482
00:28:32,142 --> 00:28:33,574
Salinas, Kansas.

483
00:28:34,537 --> 00:28:36,631
And don't say
I'm not in Kansas anymore.

484
00:28:36,827 --> 00:28:38,327
I've heard that one.

485
00:28:38,970 --> 00:28:40,426
I know exactly where I am.

486
00:28:41,004 --> 00:28:42,654
And who I'm talking to.

487
00:28:48,062 --> 00:28:49,612
Did it really happen?

488
00:28:50,227 --> 00:28:51,707
Was she ever here?

489
00:28:52,244 --> 00:28:56,094
Or was it something programmed
into me in some basement somewhere?

490
00:28:56,999 --> 00:28:58,069
Doesn't matter.

491
00:28:58,420 --> 00:28:59,620
She was right.

492
00:28:59,980 --> 00:29:02,230
They made me into something better.

493
00:29:03,053 --> 00:29:04,753
You try to be your best.

494
00:29:05,941 --> 00:29:06,786
Yes.

495
00:29:07,696 --> 00:29:11,749
Even if I could, I don't know
if I want to be the man I was before.

496
00:29:11,917 --> 00:29:13,178
I understand.

497
00:29:15,036 --> 00:29:16,170
You do, don't you?

498
00:29:16,338 --> 00:29:18,143
I'm afraid of Caroline.

499
00:29:18,268 --> 00:29:20,518
If she comes back, where will I go?

500
00:29:21,637 --> 00:29:23,052
I don't want to fall asleep.

501
00:29:23,697 --> 00:29:25,221
Even for a little while.

502
00:29:26,353 --> 00:29:27,792
You're awake now.

503
00:29:28,751 --> 00:29:32,061
And so am I.
That's what they didn't expect.

504
00:29:32,769 --> 00:29:35,147
They were going to use me as cover,
but they didn't get a chance

505
00:29:35,316 --> 00:29:36,616
to reprogram me.

506
00:29:37,424 --> 00:29:40,231
They've created someone
who can bring them down.

507
00:29:40,356 --> 00:29:42,049
And that's what I'm going to do.

508
00:29:42,495 --> 00:29:44,662
There's still time.
We can make it to the hearings.

509
00:29:44,787 --> 00:29:46,237
We can expose them.

510
00:29:47,150 --> 00:29:49,245
And then we can be who we are.

511
00:29:50,075 --> 00:29:53,337
We can be who we decide to be.

512
00:29:58,635 --> 00:30:00,715
Okay. Fire when ready.

513
00:30:08,806 --> 00:30:10,349
I got nothing on Echo.

514
00:30:12,372 --> 00:30:13,622
That's unusual.

515
00:30:14,304 --> 00:30:16,704
I think your senator's
filibustering.

516
00:30:18,110 --> 00:30:19,110
Wait...

517
00:30:23,103 --> 00:30:24,155
What did you do?

518
00:30:58,552 --> 00:30:59,690
Daniel, stop!

519
00:31:02,826 --> 00:31:04,820
They're in your head.
You don't have to listen!

520
00:31:05,345 --> 00:31:07,573
You don't have to be
what they tell you to be.

521
00:31:08,533 --> 00:31:10,133
You can belong to you.

522
00:31:16,208 --> 00:31:17,996
- What do we see?
- Who is it?

523
00:31:18,121 --> 00:31:19,877
<i>I'm looking at a triggered sleeper.</i>

524
00:31:20,045 --> 00:31:21,545
He's not set on stun.

525
00:31:21,713 --> 00:31:24,715
- How's the other one?
- <i>Still alive.</i>

526
00:31:24,883 --> 00:31:27,134
But spiking on every front.
I don't think she can match him.

527
00:31:27,302 --> 00:31:30,262
Get our new girlfriend
to switch him off or bye-bye, Echo.

528
00:31:30,531 --> 00:31:31,578
Roger that.

529
00:31:33,516 --> 00:31:35,421
You hacked into my system.

530
00:31:37,952 --> 00:31:40,481
- You stole Perrin's brain map.
- You're trying to kill Echo.

531
00:31:41,920 --> 00:31:43,484
- So we're even?
- Not even.

532
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:46,278
Not even close.
Shut him down. Now.

533
00:31:47,451 --> 00:31:49,615
- Do you know who Echo really is?
- She's a friend.

534
00:31:49,783 --> 00:31:50,847
Friend?

535
00:31:51,392 --> 00:31:52,450
That shell?

536
00:31:54,091 --> 00:31:55,441
I was her friend!

537
00:31:56,149 --> 00:31:57,581
I was her best friend.

538
00:31:58,258 --> 00:32:00,196
This is what I got for it.

539
00:32:00,768 --> 00:32:02,419
This is my gift from Caroline.

540
00:32:03,145 --> 00:32:05,339
This isn't about Caroline.
This is about Echo.

541
00:32:05,507 --> 00:32:06,934
They're the same!

542
00:32:07,059 --> 00:32:10,312
Caroline has a power over people,

543
00:32:10,437 --> 00:32:13,222
and however well you wiped her,
she clearly still does!

544
00:32:13,391 --> 00:32:15,091
She has no power over...

545
00:32:15,347 --> 00:32:18,686
When was the last time
that you described a Doll as a friend?

546
00:32:20,675 --> 00:32:22,725
I know about Alpha and Ballard.

547
00:32:23,585 --> 00:32:26,360
You're saying
she doesn't have some power?

548
00:32:26,823 --> 00:32:28,779
I'm saying shut Perrin down.

549
00:32:32,034 --> 00:32:33,434
It's for the best.

550
00:32:40,703 --> 00:32:43,127
You were so close to perfect.

551
00:32:48,162 --> 00:32:49,258
You still with me?

552
00:32:49,426 --> 00:32:51,427
Is Bennett on board?
'Cause I don't see...

553
00:32:51,595 --> 00:32:53,220
- Bennett's out.
- I killed her?

554
00:32:53,999 --> 00:32:55,723
I hit her. It hurt.

555
00:32:55,891 --> 00:32:57,391
But we can't just flip him back.

556
00:32:57,667 --> 00:32:59,810
We can if we isolate
the neural path.

557
00:32:59,979 --> 00:33:02,313
- Do you know how many...
- Then shut up and work.

558
00:33:02,481 --> 00:33:03,522
I'm working.

559
00:33:03,690 --> 00:33:05,274
I wouldn't hold your breath.

560
00:33:05,442 --> 00:33:06,692
No. I wouldn't.

561
00:33:24,312 --> 00:33:25,312
Split up.

562
00:34:22,576 --> 00:34:23,477
Where is he?

563
00:34:24,081 --> 00:34:25,081
Gone.

564
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:26,772
Something else is here.

565
00:34:26,940 --> 00:34:28,602
Oh, God. Doll-speak.

566
00:34:30,944 --> 00:34:33,362
Watch her.
I'm going to go get the senator.

567
00:34:36,527 --> 00:34:37,877
Please answer me.

568
00:34:40,478 --> 00:34:42,470
Those things I said before...

569
00:34:42,892 --> 00:34:44,540
none of them were true.

570
00:34:45,264 --> 00:34:46,984
I wanted to hurt you.

571
00:34:48,446 --> 00:34:50,163
They programmed you to love me,

572
00:34:50,288 --> 00:34:53,482
but the truth is,
no one programmed me to love you.

573
00:34:54,492 --> 00:34:55,492
And I do.

574
00:34:59,118 --> 00:35:00,468
I love you, baby.

575
00:35:02,628 --> 00:35:03,726
Come with me.

576
00:35:04,905 --> 00:35:07,146
Things can be
just like they were before.

577
00:35:09,057 --> 00:35:10,657
We can be happy again.

578
00:35:13,079 --> 00:35:14,179
Like before.

579
00:35:18,990 --> 00:35:20,240
And ever after.

580
00:35:21,526 --> 00:35:22,619
That's right.

581
00:35:52,297 --> 00:35:53,624
Daniel, stop!

582
00:35:56,235 --> 00:35:57,821
She's got me locked out on this end.

583
00:35:58,949 --> 00:36:00,240
Who's your back door man?

584
00:36:01,074 --> 00:36:03,611
We'll just pretend
I didn't say that.

585
00:36:05,789 --> 00:36:07,623
- Found the worm.
- Step on it.

586
00:36:14,714 --> 00:36:15,714
Squished.

587
00:36:30,481 --> 00:36:32,319
She's broken. We have to go.

588
00:36:32,444 --> 00:36:33,597
I killed her.

589
00:36:34,565 --> 00:36:36,151
- I did this.
- It wasn't you.

590
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:37,194
It was them.

591
00:36:40,309 --> 00:36:41,743
Daniel, we have to go.

592
00:36:42,093 --> 00:36:44,118
You can still stop them,
but they're coming.

593
00:36:44,286 --> 00:36:45,328
If we don't go...

594
00:36:45,453 --> 00:36:47,913
They'll just make us forget...
forget that I killed her.

595
00:36:48,082 --> 00:36:49,295
They killed her.

596
00:36:49,420 --> 00:36:51,602
If you let them make you forget,
then you killed her.

597
00:36:51,727 --> 00:36:53,877
Can you live with that,
or can you trust me?

598
00:37:21,448 --> 00:37:22,697
Where is Mrs. Perrin?

599
00:37:28,627 --> 00:37:30,497
I apologize to the committee for...

600
00:37:36,845 --> 00:37:38,005
My wife is dead.

601
00:37:45,661 --> 00:37:48,140
I don't want to be here right now,
but I'm honestly afraid

602
00:37:48,308 --> 00:37:51,143
I may not have another chance
to tell the truth.

603
00:37:52,465 --> 00:37:55,355
I was looking for a conspiracy,
and I found something more horrible...

604
00:37:58,580 --> 00:38:02,446
The Rossum Corporation
is the most powerful medical company,

605
00:38:02,614 --> 00:38:04,573
but they are something else,
as well.

606
00:38:04,884 --> 00:38:06,734
For the past several years,

607
00:38:07,228 --> 00:38:09,369
the Rossum Corporation
has been a target.

608
00:38:10,062 --> 00:38:12,956
A target of a consortium of companies
that would stop at nothing

609
00:38:13,125 --> 00:38:16,835
to undermine Rossum and take its place
in the medical community.

610
00:38:17,161 --> 00:38:20,714
They set me on Rossum's trail,
and when I discovered the real truth,

611
00:38:21,410 --> 00:38:23,133
they put a bomb in my car.

612
00:38:26,430 --> 00:38:29,389
The car Cindy took
to stop by the family compound.

613
00:38:38,665 --> 00:38:40,609
My wife was a victim.

614
00:38:41,611 --> 00:38:43,861
There have been hundreds of others.

615
00:38:44,244 --> 00:38:46,890
This woman, Madeline Costley,
is a victim...

616
00:38:47,015 --> 00:38:50,077
of their manipulation
and her own delusions.

617
00:38:50,368 --> 00:38:51,411
What?

618
00:38:51,579 --> 00:38:54,569
There is no Dollhouse.

619
00:38:55,306 --> 00:38:59,253
There are no sex slaves,
no underground fortresses.

620
00:38:59,422 --> 00:39:02,965
Madeline Costley spent the last 3 years
in a mental institution in Canada.

621
00:39:05,094 --> 00:39:08,411
- You know I was there.
- I have the documentation to prove it.

622
00:39:08,561 --> 00:39:12,523
In fact, I have documentation
on all the companies involved in this...

623
00:39:13,154 --> 00:39:14,100
travesty.

624
00:39:15,402 --> 00:39:16,770
There is abuse here.

625
00:39:16,939 --> 00:39:19,022
Not the lurid, pulp fantasy

626
00:39:19,147 --> 00:39:21,497
they drilled
into this unstable mind,

627
00:39:23,223 --> 00:39:26,373
but something more insidious,

628
00:39:26,498 --> 00:39:31,118
something that has cost this country
more than millions,

629
00:39:31,565 --> 00:39:33,078
and has cost me...

630
00:39:39,290 --> 00:39:40,293
... everything.

631
00:39:48,031 --> 00:39:50,220
This hearing is adjourned
until further notice.

632
00:40:03,941 --> 00:40:07,504
These men are from the FBI.
They need to speak with you.

633
00:40:15,281 --> 00:40:16,934
No. Echo's just gone.

634
00:40:17,059 --> 00:40:19,306
And we're certain she wasn't
apprehended with Perrin?

635
00:40:19,431 --> 00:40:21,616
My sources say no.
They don't have her.

636
00:40:21,741 --> 00:40:24,001
- And Mr. Ballard?
- Still no word.

637
00:40:27,606 --> 00:40:30,278
Are we sure
this is such a great idea?

638
00:40:31,347 --> 00:40:32,909
I am sensing tension...

639
00:40:33,034 --> 00:40:34,639
of the palpable sort.

640
00:40:34,808 --> 00:40:35,849
Just lie back.

641
00:40:36,018 --> 00:40:37,392
Finding him obstinate, are we?

642
00:40:39,273 --> 00:40:41,573
- This is so weird.
- This is so weird.

643
00:40:42,206 --> 00:40:45,150
Seriously, just a few more days.

644
00:40:45,327 --> 00:40:47,235
I could help analyzing
Perrin's brain map.

645
00:40:47,727 --> 00:40:50,489
It wouldn't be a second opinion.
It would be the same opinion twice.

646
00:40:50,657 --> 00:40:53,691
There's more to analyze?
I thought we knew his function.

647
00:40:53,816 --> 00:40:55,635
To inoculate Rossum
against further scrutiny.

648
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:56,742
More than that.

649
00:40:56,867 --> 00:40:59,820
He's talking about new regulation,
which, inevitably, he'll oversee.

650
00:40:59,945 --> 00:41:01,625
Rossum will be creating
their own laws.

651
00:41:01,793 --> 00:41:03,478
Ah, good throw, Boyd,

652
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:07,255
but still doesn't win you
the giant stuffed panda.

653
00:41:09,797 --> 00:41:11,343
It looks like Bennett somehow

654
00:41:11,512 --> 00:41:13,553
rigged his SNS
into his higher functions.

655
00:41:13,786 --> 00:41:15,514
- Meaning?
- Let's just say...

656
00:41:15,683 --> 00:41:18,100
It's an awful lot of ambition
for a junior senator.

657
00:41:18,280 --> 00:41:19,980
I was going to say that.

658
00:41:31,136 --> 00:41:33,782
- Did I fall asleep?
- For a little while.

659
00:41:33,951 --> 00:41:34,950
Shall I go now?

660
00:41:35,119 --> 00:41:36,743
For the love of God, yes.

661
00:41:40,122 --> 00:41:42,937
So, what are you saying?
They're manufacturing a president?

662
00:41:43,502 --> 00:41:45,877
- Wouldn't be the first time.
- Delightful.

663
00:41:46,237 --> 00:41:49,172
Well, before the fascist takeover,
we need to find Echo.

664
00:41:49,358 --> 00:41:52,708
She's lost in the world in Doll-state,
utterly helpless.

665
00:41:52,948 --> 00:41:55,262
I want every resource
engaged in her recovery.

666
00:41:55,431 --> 00:41:56,388
And Madeline?

667
00:41:56,557 --> 00:41:57,537
Poor girl.

668
00:41:58,476 --> 00:42:00,475
I'm afraid there's nothing more
we can do.

669
00:42:01,160 --> 00:42:03,060
You don't have to be afraid.

670
00:42:04,195 --> 00:42:05,699
I know how you feel.

671
00:42:07,393 --> 00:42:10,297
I know what it's like
to be betrayed.

672
00:42:11,948 --> 00:42:13,248
To be abandoned.

673
00:42:17,566 --> 00:42:18,866
She's out there.

674
00:42:20,978 --> 00:42:23,011
They're all out there,

675
00:42:23,681 --> 00:42:25,281
and we're left behind.

676
00:42:27,989 --> 00:42:28,989
Alone.

677
00:42:40,469 --> 00:42:42,119
No one should be alone.

